        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 24 at 3:37AM CST by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 337 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 17 miles northwest of Broken Bow to 7
miles northwest of Bagwell, or extending from 36 miles west of De
Queen to 15 miles northwest of Clarksville, moving northeast at 55
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Idabel, Broken Bow, Manchester, Wright City, Valliant, Millerton,
Garvin, Oak Hill, Glover, Golden, Holly Creek, Hochatown, Mount
Herman, Farmers Hill, Sherwood, Slim, Eagletown, Albion, Rufe and
Silver City.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
